<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-05-01T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-05-01T12:00:00-05:00" n="37" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d37">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/1722</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SWG1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-01T17:00:00+00:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 1, 1915, 5 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 7 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>137. Reported on authority which I believe reliable that Italy signed
                            agreement with Allies last Tuesday.<note n="1" xml:id="d37fn1">i. e.,
                                April 27.</note> Terms of agreement not known yet but are supposed
                            to accord guaranties of territorial extension to Italy in return for
                            military support of cause of Allies.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_SWG1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sharp</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>